        <p>Cherie‚Äôs thought was that creative professionals have a lot of different ways they collect images and inspirations, but they all live in different places‚ÄîPinterest, Instagram, Dropbox, desktop folders, etc. This is frustrating and slows down their creative process‚Äìespecially when they need to create moodboards to share ideas with clients. She wanted to create a platform that would enable creatives to put all of their pins and photos into one place. This would ultimately build a community of curated content that other creatives could benefit from. She also wanted to incorporate a way to help creatives organize and quickly find their content, whether through custom labels, tags, notes, or color swatches.</p>

        <h3 class="article__heading">02. Process</h3>
        <p>I facilitated a five day Product Design Sprint with Cherie and another designer, based off of Google Ventures' method. We use Sprints to mitigate the risk inherent in bringing a new product to market. We capture the riskiest assumptions that we want to validate or invalidate, to ultimately give us the confidence we need determine how best we should move forward. We ran through the Understand, Diverge, and Converge phases to establish context, diverge on different ideas, and converge on a solution that we ultimately prototyped and user tested with potential customers on the fifth and final day.</p>

