        <p>On the fifth and final day of the Sprint we popped over to The Wing in London and showed our prototype to five creative professionals: two graphic designers, one branding designer, one fashion designer, and one floral stylist. We sat with each designer for 45 minutes, using the first 15 minutes to ask some background questions, and the remaining time to go through the prototype.</p>

        <p>Overall, we received positive feedback and the users we interviewed were interested in the idea. They unanimously loved the ability to import their photos from all their various collections‚Äìespecially Instagram, which right now takes the most effort to organize. They also unanimously validated the need for the different filtering types to search through their library of images. Where they split was on the moodboard creation. Half of them found it convenient, while the other half said that they would stick to their current method because it would be easier for them to do that instead of adopting a new tool.</p>

