        <p>This was all the information we needed to decide upon a path forward. Due to the mixed reviews from this first round of feedback, we determined that the moodboard creation was not a necessity for launch, which significantly reduced the scope and time to market. We determined that the next step would be to do a development spike on the import feature, to see what opportunities and limitations exist when trying to import images and data from Instagram and Pinterest. From there, Cherie would have a better understanding of the technical feasibility of this well-received feature, and would be able to determine how best to move forward.</p>

        <p>In conclusion, we saved Cherie a ton of money and time! She came in with a very strong sense that the moodboard component of her tool would be the key differentiator, but we invalidated that idea in favor of a robust import feature. After going through the Sprint process, she learned the value of research and rapid validation, and quickly became a firm believer in incorporating them into her process moving forward to inform her product roadmap.</p>
